<p>Ukrainian drones struck the Orenburg gas processing plant in southern Russia overnight into Sunday, igniting a fire at a workshop, local officials said [abcnews.go.com#1][dawn.com#1]. The facility is described by multiple outlets as the world&#x27;s largest of its kind [dw.com#1]. Emergency services worked to extinguish the blaze, according to the Orenburg regional governor [dawn.com#1]. Kazakhstan’s energy ministry said the plant subsequently suspended its intake of gas from Kazakhstan following the strike [straitstimes.com#1][ndtv.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/wHyGnPov5Ho6zjc3wp3WAwfxiFWoqAf1Ni98fmtYNpU7l8SvhHKNO3jrgvIjFKBtHzv3gci3YCMasaDU1uF0v80oRQRFbY_Jm2Eo6uAAkmal' alt='File: A liquefied natural gas facility in Russia.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Long-range strike: The attack was reported as a long-range strike deep inside Russia, underscoring Ukraine’s ability to hit critical energy infrastructure far from the front lines [dw.com#1].</li><li>Air defenses: Moscow said air defenses downed 45 Ukrainian drones during the overnight wave of attacks, highlighting the scale of the barrage [firstpost.com#1].</li><li>Earlier attempt: Earlier this month, drones attempted to hit an industrial facility in Orsk, with unverified video showing an object striking the Orsknefteorgsintez refinery [dawn.com#1].</li><li>Strategic aim: Ukraine has intensified strikes on refineries and energy sites since August to disrupt fuel supplies and reduce Moscow&#x27;s wartime revenues [dawn.com#1][firstpost.com#1].</li><li>US political context: Amid the broader conflict, President Trump hinted Kyiv may have to cede territory in potential negotiations, adding diplomatic complexity to the battlefield dynamics [ndtv.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Orenburg regional governor Yevgeny Solntsev: Said no plant employees were hurt, and that emergency services were working to put out the fire after the workshop was hit. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1949910/ukrainian-drones-cause-fire-at-russian-gas-plant-governor-says'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>Kazakhstan’s Energy Ministry: Reported that the Orenburg plant suspended its intake of gas from Kazakhstan following the strike. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/Giant-Russian-gas-plant-suspends-intake-from-Kazakhstan-after-Ukrainian-drone-strike'>The Straits Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1949910/ukrainian-drones-cause-fire-at-russian-gas-plant-governor-says'>Ukrainian drones cause fire at Russian gas plant, governor says</a> - dawn.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/ukrainian-drones-strike-major-russian-gas-plant-126657369'>Ukrainian drones strike major Russian gas plant</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/ukraine-hits-russian-gas-plant-as-trump-hints-kyiv-will-have-to-cede-land-9484562#publisher=newsstand'>Ukraine Hits Russian Gas Plant As Trump Hints Kyiv Will Have To Cede Land</a> - ndtv.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/Giant-Russian-gas-plant-suspends-intake-from-Kazakhstan-after-Ukrainian-drone-strike'>Giant Russian gas plant suspends intake from Kazakhstan after Ukrainian drone strike</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/ukraine-updates-russian-gas-plant-hit-in-long-range-strike/live-74409773'>Ukraine updates: Russian gas plant hit in long-range strike</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/ukraine-escalates-energy-war-strikes-russias-gas-complex-13943422.html'>Ukraine escalates energy war, strikes Russia’s gas complex</a> - firstpost.com</li></ul>